2026-05-11 02:45 IST - Live Render Express diagnosis

Current backend origin:
- https://pdf-toolkit-api.onrender.com

Observed live responses:
- `/health`: connection reset from this environment.
- `/docs`: HTTP 404, `x-powered-by: Express`, body `Cannot GET /docs`.
- `/openapi.json`: HTTP 404, `x-powered-by: Express`, body `Cannot GET /openapi.json`.
- `/api/pdf`: HTTP 404, `x-powered-by: Express`, body `Cannot GET /api/pdf`.

Exact root cause:
- Render is running a Node/Express service, not the FastAPI app in `backend/app/main.py`.
- The backend directory contained stray Node deployment markers (`backend/package.json` and `backend/package-lock.json`) with only `lucide-react`; these have been removed to prevent Render auto-detecting the backend as Node.
- The correct Render service must be Python 3, root directory `backend`, start command `python -m uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`.

